    { "id": "LN_01", "section": "learn", "difficulty": 0, "type": "concept_card", "title": "The Associative Property", "content": "When multiplying three numbers, you can change which two you multiply first. (2×3)×5 = 2×(3×5). Both = 30. The grouping changes, but the product doesn't." },
